<cell id="cell-0"><cell_type>markdown</cell_type># Phase 6 — Improvement Strategies: Adaptive & Progressive Resolution

Two improvement strategies designed to close the gap between cheap (224 px)
and expensive (518 px) inference:

| Strategy | Idea |
|----------|------|
| **Adaptive Resolution** | Global low-res pass → find uncertain patches → high-res patch inference → confidence-weighted merge |
| **Progressive Refinement** | Coarse-to-fine pyramid (224→336→518 px) — blend depth maps using confidence at each level |

Both strategies target **depth map quality** (the main weakness at low
resolution) while keeping camera poses accurate via the final or highest-res
pass.

**Baseline comparison:** pure 224 px, pure 518 px, adaptive, progressive.</cell id="cell-0">
