<cell id="cell-22"><cell_type>markdown</cell_type>## 10 — Trajectories: All Methods vs GT</cell id="cell-22">
<cell id="cell-23">from src.metrics import align_trajectories_umeyama

def cam_centers(ext):
    R = ext[:, :3, :3]; t = ext[:, :3, 3]
    return -np.einsum("nij,nj->ni", R.transpose(0,2,1), t)

c_gt   = gt_extrinsics[:, :3, 3]   # GT positions (mocap)
c_224  = cam_centers(out_224["extrinsic"])
c_518  = cam_centers(out_518["extrinsic"])
c_adap = cam_centers(out_adapt["extrinsic"])
c_prog = cam_centers(out_prog["extrinsic"])

# Align all to GT using the 518-px scale factor
R_al, t_al, s_al = align_trajectories_umeyama(c_518, c_gt, with_scale=True)

def align(c):
    return s_al * (R_al @ c.T).T + t_al

fig = go.Figure()

def traj(c, name, color, dash="solid"):
    return go.Scatter3d(
        x=c[:,0], y=c[:,1], z=c[:,2],
        mode="lines+markers",
        name=name,
        line=dict(color=color, width=3, dash=dash),
        marker=dict(size=3),
    )

fig.add_trace(traj(c_gt,          "Ground truth",       "black"))
fig.add_trace(traj(align(c_224),  "224 px",             "steelblue", "dash"))
fig.add_trace(traj(align(c_518),  "518 px",             "firebrick"))
fig.add_trace(traj(align(c_adap), "Adaptive",           "darkorange", "dot"))
fig.add_trace(traj(align(c_prog), "Progressive",        "forestgreen", "longdash"))

fig.update_layout(
    title=f"Trajectories — TUM-VI {SEQUENCE}",
    scene=dict(xaxis_title="X", yaxis_title="Y", zaxis_title="Z",
               aspectmode="data"),
)
fig.show()</cell id="cell-23">
<cell id="cell-24"><cell_type>markdown</cell_type>## Discussion

### What to look for

**Adaptive resolution** should:
- Match or beat 518-px ATE in depth-uncertain regions.
- Be faster than pure 518-px (skips patches where confidence is already high).
- Number of patches applied (`patches_used`) tells you how much of the scene was uncertain.

**Progressive refinement** should:
- Blend depth from coarser levels, damping outliers that occur at a single scale.
- Final poses are 518-px quality; depth is a weighted composite.
- Total time ≈ time(224) + time(336) + time(518) because all three are sequential.

### Expected trade-off table

| Method       | ATE     | Time    | Memory  |
|--------------|---------|---------|---------|
| 224 px       | worst   | fastest | lowest  |
| Adaptive     | ≈ 518   | medium  | low-med |
| Progressive  | ≈ 518   | 3×224   | medium  |
| 518 px       | best    | slowest | highest |

### Limitations

- Adaptive patching only refines depth; camera poses still come from the
  global 224-px pass which may not be as accurate as 518-px.
- Progressive refinement tripling the inference cost may not be worthwhile
  if the 518-px baseline already saturates the T4's memory budget.
- A proper learned uncertainty map (e.g. from the VGGT confidence head)
  would outperform the naive low-confidence patch heuristic.</cell id="cell-24">
